      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm seeing a 500 error on our /api/v1/checkout/complete endpoint. it only happens intermittently, maybe 5% of requests. here are the recent logs from the production cluster:\n\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] ERROR: Internal Server Error - RequestID: f82a-4491-b212\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] stacktrace: \n    at CheckoutService.processPayment (checkout_service.py:142)\n    at OrderController.commitOrder (order_controller.py:88)\n    at app.handle_request (app.py:210)\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] DEBUG: ConnectionTimeoutError: Database connection pool exhausted while attempting to acquire connection for transaction 'tx_99283'.\n\ncan you help me figure out what's likely causing this?",
